OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1776077823
OL,3,CStroud Lido: Flashmob forms for
OL,4,Ccampaign to reopen pool
OL,6,FThe last option is to close the lido
OL,7,Fand explore funding options while
OL,8,Facknowledging the it cannot open for
OL,9,Fthe 2026 season.
OL,11,FDuring the closure period, the council
OL,12,Fwould engage the local community and
OL,13,Fvoluntary organisations.
OL,15,FThis would involve working
OL,16,Fcollaboratively to allow community-led
OL,17,Ffundraising aimed at securing the
OL,18,Fthird party match funded capital
OL,19,Finvestment needed to reopen the lido.
OL,21,FWhen will a decision be made?
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/11
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
